  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      CLAG-M is an active, well tolerated regimen in acute myelogenous leukemia. Each of the agents
      is active in Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia (ALL) as well. The current trial will determine the
      efficacy of the regimen in patients with relapsed ALL.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will receive standard dose CLAG-M (cladribine, cytarabine, mitoxantrone,
      filgrastim). Standard support care will be given. Efficacy will be assessed through bone
      marrow examinations and blood tests.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
